  "eventMetadata": {
    "context_description": "President Trump's rejection on April 29 of Iran's proposal to reopen the Strait of Hormuz and extend the ceasefire while postponing nuclear negotiations has solidified trader consensus against a comprehensive US-Iran nuclear deal by June 30, pricing \"No\" at 70.5%. Indirect talks mediated by Pakistan, building on April 12 negotiations, remain stalled over Iran's nuclear enrichment levels and US demands for verifiable curbs before easing the blockade or sanctions. Recent firm messaging from Washington underscores no compromise on the nuclear issue, prompting Tehran to reassess amid ongoing military pressures. With no breakthrough in the past week and historical JCPOA revival patterns showing protracted timelines, traders anticipate continued impasse despite diplomatic channels staying open.",
    "context_requires_regen": true,
    "context_updated_at": "2026-05-01T08:48:47.675Z"
